                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I can sympathize Columbine. I remember when I started playing EQ and even a couple of years later I remember porting into EC and it was just a kick to run through the zone looking at things.
<br />

<br />
I can also sympathize about the friends. My guild is fragmented across many games. Some are still playing EQ and - presumably - enjoying it. I don't know how many since I haven't logged into EQ for more than 15 minutes for nearly a month. Some - including the guild leader - have gone to EQ2 and seem to be having fun. Some - myself included - have gone to WoW and are loving it. Others have gone to Planetside, SWG, CoH or ... you name it. We were a family type guild and at one point we'd have maybe 30-40 people on in the evenings. When I left EQ we would have maybe 6 or 7. A very sad state.
<br />

<br />
I don't understand the religious zeal your friends have, unless it's just that they like you so much that they're trying to convince you that the game they're playing is the best and you should join them there. It could be a lot worse. They could have moved and left no forwarding address <img src="images/smiles/icon_wink.gif" alt="icon_wink.gif" border="0" />
<br />

<br />
You have my best wishes on resolving the conflict, but it won't be easy.</span><span class="postbody"><br />_________________<br />Max
<br />
<a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=368646" target="_blank" class="postlink">Fanamax the Enchanter</a></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
