                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">This is actually very similar to a lot of stories you hear from people who are making the transition from high school to college.  During this time period a lot of long standing friendships are tested and stressed in ways that they weren't before.  The golden time when all your relationships with other people easily meshed together is over and it won't come back because things are changing.  Compromise becomes the name of the game and it's a two way street.  It sounds like your friends may not be aware of how you feel about all of this.  If you're going to come to a compromise, you'll have to let them know.  Communication is a strong key in any compromise.</span><span class="postbody"><br />_________________<br /><a href="http://wow.allakhazam.com/profile.html?37749" target="_blank" class="postlink"><img src="http://www.blaynesucks.com/images/Bellanfear.gif" border="0" /></a>
<br />
<a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=811231" target="_blank" class="postlink">Bellanfear</a>, lvl 70.468 EQ1 Enchanter, Retired</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
